          <para>Command each spoiler actuator individually to FULL UP and FULL DOWN using CMS override commands.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Measure actuator stroke length manually using calibrated linear gauge (Ref: TOOL-SR-777-LIN). Compare extension to AMM limits:  
            - Inboard spoilers: 14.000 ± 0.050 in  
            - Midboard spoilers: 13.750 ± 0.060 in  
            - Outboard spoilers: 13.500 ± 0.070 in
          </para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Cycle each spoiler panel through three full stroke motions. Monitor CMS feedback for synchronization errors between redundant SCU channels (< 1% deviation allowed).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Record actuator extension data. Identify any units that exceed allowable mismatch threshold (> 0.100 in deviation between symmetrical spoilers).</para>
        </step>
