        <crewRequirement>3 Technicians (lifting/handling crew)</crewRequirement>
      </taskRequirement>

      <preliminaryRqmts>
        <preliminaryRqmtsDescr>Surface removed from aircraft and mounted in approved mass balance fixture (Ref: AMM ZONE 450 for rudder, ZONE 430/440 for elevators, ZONE 420 for ailerons).</preliminaryRqmtsDescr>

        <safety>
          <warning>
            Flight control surfaces are heavy and unbalanced until weights installed. Ensure surfaces are safely secured during handling.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Use only OEM-specified weights. Substitute materials are prohibited due to density and thermal expansion properties.
          </caution>
          <note>
            Environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) must be recorded as they affect balance calculations. Surface must be clean and dry.
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Mount control surface horizontally on precision pivoted balance rig, ensuring no binding or resistance.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Measure neutral balance angle. Surface must come to rest within ±0.5° of defined neutral CG axis without external force.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Apply moment calculation using provided balance charts: moment = (applied force × lever arm distance).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>If neutral not achieved, adjust weights using certified OEM mass balance kits (Ref: IPC 27-XX-00, Balance Parts).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Re-measure after each adjustment until surface neutrally balances within specified moment range. Record final balance condition.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Inspect attachment of all balance weights. Torque fasteners to 45 in-lb per AMM 20-50-00, and apply thread locking compound (CPC-911-LOCTITE).</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Secure surface for reinstallation. Apply tamper-evident seal to balance weight attach points. Restore surface to installation readiness condition.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Record balance data, temperature/humidity conditions, adjustment details, and technician IDs in Flight Control Mass Balance Log (ATA 05-00-00).</para>
        </step>
      </closeProcedure>

