        <preliminaryRqmtsDescr>Aircraft parked, engines off, hydraulic systems depressurized. Door areas cleared of ground support equipment. Access panels on door assist system removed as needed.</preliminaryRqmtsDescr>

        <safety>
          <warning>
            Passenger doors under pneumatic assist can open rapidly. Keep personnel clear of door swing arc during any deployment sequence.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Do not cycle door locking/unlocking lever without verifying door pressurization vent system is open; internal pressure may cause door blast.
          </caution>
          <note>
            Deployment tests must include full manual override mode to validate mechanical linkages independent of assist systems.
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Ensure external vent valves are open and pressure differential is equalized. Inspect visual indicators for locked/unlocked status.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Move internal locking handle to UNLOCKED. Confirm green indicators at viewing ports.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Lift internal door handle to initiate opening sequence. Allow door to free travel under gravity and assist force. Observe motion for smoothness, binding, or oscillation.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Fully open door to mechanical hold-open position. Inspect assist cylinder for full extension and leak-free operation.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Engage manual mode override lever. Confirm pneumatic assist bypass. Close door manually through full arc. Check for excessive force, misalignment, or abnormal resistance.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Re-engage powered assist mode. Close and lock door. Confirm external latch pins fully engaged.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Install any removed access panels. Remove safety flags. Complete locking indicator inspection. Remove GSE as required. Confirm aircraft "Ready for Flight" configuration.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Log operational check, manual override check, and locking system inspection findings in maintenance record (ATA 05-00-00).</para>
        </step>
      </closeProcedure>

